#compdef hunter
# =============================================================================
# hunter — rabite0's "fastest file manager in the galaxy!" — a
#           Unix-only terminal file manager built on termion (the
#           Unix-pure-Rust terminal manipulation library).  hunter
#           implements the classic THREE-PANE MILLER-COLUMNS file-
#           browser interface (parent dir / current dir / preview),
#           pioneered by NeXTSTEP's File Viewer (1989) and famously
#           used in macOS Finder, ranger (Python), nnn (C), and lf
#           (Go).  hunter's distinctive features:
#             - Asynchronous file listing (won't block on slow NFS,
#               disconnected USB drives, or huge directories)
#             - Live preview pane (text files via syntect highlighting,
#               images via sixel / kitty graphics protocols, video
#               via ffmpeg thumbnails)
#             - File-type icons (Nerd Font icon mapping)
#             - Tabs (multiple parallel browsing contexts)
#             - Bookmarks (Vim-style: `'a`, `'b`, etc.)
#             - Trash-cli integration (move to trash via TRASH_DIR)
#             - File-search via ripgrep / silver-searcher integration
#             - Configurable previewers (lua-defined per-MIME-type
#               preview commands)
#             - MIME detection via tree_magic_fork
#           Originally created in 2018-2019 as a personal Rust
#           alternative to ranger after rabite0 wanted faster
#           directory navigation without Python startup overhead.
#
# Author:  rabite0 (https://github.com/rabite0) — independent Rust
#          developer, prolific Reddit r/rust contributor; hunter is
#          rabite0's primary maintained project.
# Source:  https://github.com/rabite0/hunter
# CLI:     src/main.rs (uses clap 2.x App/Arg builder + termion
#                        for the entire visible interface)
# Library: redox-os/termion
#          ("Bindless library for low-level handling, manipulating
#           and reading information about terminals" — Redox OS
#           project's PURE-RUST UNIX-ONLY terminal manipulation
#           library, distinct from crossterm-rs/crossterm which is
#           cross-platform; the Rust parallel to Go's gdamore/tcell
#           and TypeScript-Node's blessed R536.)
# License: WTFPL
# Status:  Active — 1337+ stars on rabite0/hunter (a META-number for
#          a hacker tool!); termion itself is 2166+ stars on
#          redox-os/termion (continuous development since 2016 by
#          Redox OS and 50+ contributors).
#
